"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524472","Home Office","false","2016-06-15","<p>Home Office officials have been involved in discussions with the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills to ensure that any conditions relating to access to Higher Education for those granted humanitarian protection satisfy our international obligations.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-15T11:06:14.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524472/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524472/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-10","Asylum: Higher Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills on access to higher education for people who have been granted humanitarian protection.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","40213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524473","Department for International Development","false","2016-06-15","<p>The St Helena Airport was certificated by Air Safety Support International on 10 May 2016 and is open. As a result of turbulence and wind shear identified on the northern approach, the certification confirms the airport is classed as Category C, which requires certain conditions to be met by airlines and aircraft proposing to use the airport. Work is underway to establish commercial air services.</p>","New Forest West","Sir Desmond Swayne",,"2016-06-15T15:30:17.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524473/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524473/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-10","St Helena: Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of the operational readiness of St Helena Airport; and when she expects commercial operations at that airport to commence.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","40233"
