"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524221","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-21","<p>The source was the Hull Daily Mail on the 4th February 2016. The full article can be found through the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.hulldailymail.co.uk/Hull-people-happy-UK-average-official-statistics/story-28672567-detail/story.html" target="_blank">http://www.hulldailymail.co.uk/Hull-people-happy-UK-average-official-statistics/story-28672567-detail/story.html</a></p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2016-06-21T13:31:39.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524221/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524221/answer","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524221/answer/previousversion/3912","Biography information for Greg Clark","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-09","Kingston upon Hull City Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Oral Answer of 6 June 2016, Official Report, column 825, what the source is for the comments attributed to the Leader of Hull City Council.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","40188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524222","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-15","<p>Criminal proceedings connected to the subject matter of the Leveson Inquiry, including the appeals process, have not yet been completed. We‎ have always been clear that these cases must conclude before we consider Part 2 of the Inquiry.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-06-15T12:37:06.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524222/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524222/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-09","Culture, Ethics and Practices of the Press Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what timetable he has set for commencing the second stage of the Leveson Inquiry.","false","Biography information for George Kerevan","East Lothian","George Kerevan","40192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524223","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-17","<p>The UK currently fields the Trident Mk4 warhead as part of the Trident Strategic Weapons System. In order to ensure continuity of the Mk4-based capability, the Mk4A Arming, Fuzing and Firing system is a non-nuclear component being introduced into the UK Trident warhead to replace a similar component. The Mk4A programme will not increase the destructive power of the warhead.</p><p> </p><p>Approval to procure the new Arming, Firing and Fuzing mechanisms, to manage obsolescence in Mk4 and to adopt a Mk4A component was given in January 2006. I am withholding further details of the date of the Mk4A component's entry into service, the cost of the Mk4A programme and the extension in operational life expected for the purposes of safeguarding national security.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","40194 ; 40195 ; 40196 ; 40197 ; 40198","2016-06-17T13:39:36.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524223/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524223/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-09","Trident Missiles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the budget is of the Mk4A upgrade programme.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","40193"
