"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523940","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-16","<p>The Climate Change Act commits the UK to reduce emissions by at least 80% in 2050 from 1990 levels. The Government recognises that carbon savings associated with domestic hot water have an important role to play in meeting this target. That is why the Government confirmed its continuing commitment to support the transition to low-carbon heating in the UK, when it announced its intention for spending on the Renewable Heat Incentive schemes to rise from £430 million in 2015/16 to £1.15 billion in 2020/21. The Renewable Heat Incentive supports the transition from conventional forms of space and water heating to renewable sources as a way of delivering emission reductions.</p><p> </p><p>One of the best ways to cut emissions and bills is to help consumers identify where they are wasting energy. That is why we have mandated the rollout of smart meters to every household in Britain by the end of 2020 and why we are also looking at the performance of boilers and conventional heating systems.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-16T15:22:39.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523940/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523940/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523940/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523940/answer/previousversion/3395","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-08","Greenhouse Gas Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment she has made of potential steps to reduce greenhouse gas emissions associated with domestic hot water production.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","40033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523941","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-16","<p>In preparation for our new emissions reduction plan we are working with colleagues across government to identify action that will cut emissions cost effectively. Our new plan will set out our proposals for meeting our carbon budgets and decarbonising through the 2020s. It will be published in due course.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-16T15:24:16.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523941/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523941/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523941/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-08","Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will publish a plan setting out how all government departments plan to contribute to reducing the UK's carbon emissions.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523942","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave the hon. Member for Easington on 8 June 2016 to Question 38958:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-06-03/38958/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-06-03/38958/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-16T15:23:34.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523942/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523942/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-08","Mining: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, with reference to the Answer of 8 March 2007 to Question 125573 and paragraph 1.21 of the National Audit Office's report, HC360, 1995-96, what the reasons are for the difference in the figures given in those documents for the Government's guarantee of the Mineworker's Pension Scheme.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","40047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523944","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-16","<p>In 2013, an estimated 89TWh of energy was used for heating water in UK domestic properties [1] and was responsible 18 MtCO2e of greenhouse gas emissions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em><strong>[1]</strong></em><em> Energy consumption from Energy Consumption in the UK table 3.05. Emissions calculation based on emissions factors consistent with the UK Greenhouse Gas Inventory. </em></p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-16T15:23:54.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523944/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523944/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523944/answer/previousversion/3394","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-08","Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate she has made of the total (a) energy consumption and (b) amount of greenhouse gas emitted by domestic properties for heating water in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","40032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523946","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-14","<p>The objective of the reformed Common Fisheries Policy is that all stocks will be fished at or below their respective Maximum Sustainable Yield by 2020. We expect to see proposals for a North Sea multi-annual plan soon which will provide the regulatory framework for the management of multi-species fisheries in the North Sea.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-14T16:53:59.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523946/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523946/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-08","Fishing Catches: North Sea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether she plans to support fishing any stocks at a higher level than the maximum sustainable yield level in the forthcoming negotiations on the multi-annual plan to manage North Sea fish stocks.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","40038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523947","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-13","<p>Defra, in conjunction with the Devolved Administrations of Scotland and Wales, fund the UK Cetacean Strandings Investigation Programme (CSIP), which investigates the causes of cetacean strandings around the UK.</p><p> </p><p>Between 2006 and 2014 a total of 4838 cetaceans (whales, dolphins, porpoises) were stranded around the UK (English, Welsh, Scottish, and Northern Ireland) coast. 147 of these were successfully refloated. The 2015 data has not yet been published. This will be available in due course on the CSIP website, where the annual reports for preceding years are already available.</p><p> </p><p>The published annual strandings data, shown below, may also be subject to change where additional strandings information is reported after publication.</p><p> </p><p>Although not part of its formal remit, data on stranded seals has been collected by CSIP in recent years. Since 2010 2185 dead stranded seals have been recorded.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>No. of UK Cetacean Strandings</p></td><td><p>No. of UK Cetacean Live Strandings</p></td><td><p>No. of UK Cetaceans Refloated</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006</p></td><td><p>718</p></td><td><p>31</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>536</p></td><td><p>41</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>566</p></td><td><p>83</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>422</p></td><td><p>39</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>277</p></td><td><p>27</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>600</p></td><td><p>86</p></td><td><p>29</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>562</p></td><td><p>75</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>595</p></td><td><p>38</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>562</p></td><td><p>55</p></td><td><p>27</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>4838</p></td><td><p>475</p></td><td><p>147</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-13T16:59:46.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523947/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523947/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-08","Cetaceans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many whales, dolphins and other aquatic mammals have been beached on British shores in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","39933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523948","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-14","<p>The UK Government is committed to assisting our Overseas Territories (OTs) in protecting their biodiversity. Territory Governments are constitutionally responsible for the conservation of their natural environments and we work in partnership with them to provide support, including through access to technical advice, expertise and training and through the Overseas Territories Climate and Environment Programme (Darwin Plus).</p><p> </p><p>Preventing the establishment of invasive alien species and eradicating or controlling invasive species is one of our priorities in supporting biodiversity conservation in the OTs. Defra has funded various projects on biosecurity, bio-control and the spread of non-native species in the OTs, including an RSPB-led Darwin Plus project which included work to improve Pitcairn’s biosecurity legislation. Defra officials stand ready to consider any requests from Pitcairn’s Government for technical assistance, advice or expertise on biosecurity matters or in respect of Pitcairn’s biosecurity legislation.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-06-14T15:25:46.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523948/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523948/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-08","Environment Protection: Pitcairn Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what technical assistance her Department has offered to the government of the Pitcairn Islands to help ensure that its draft biosecurity legislation meets best practice.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","39960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523950","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-17","We maintain a close dialogue with our international partners on terrorism and kidnapping, both on a bilateral basis and through international fora. G7 leaders have recently reaffirmed their commitment not to pay ransoms to terrorists, to protect the lives of our nationals, including by reducing terrorist groups access to funding. We do not comment on individual cases.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-06-17T12:26:20.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523950/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523950/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","Philippines: Hostage Taking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Canadian counterpart on steps to secure the release of foreign hostages held by Muslim extremists in the Philippines.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523951","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-17","<p>The UK-China Human Rights Dialogue is an important forum for us to raise the full range of our human rights concerns, including organ harvesting, with the Chinese authorities. We were not able to hold the Dialogue in April as initially scheduled, but we aim to hold it soon. In the meantime, we continue to discuss human rights issues with the Chinese, most recently when the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), met the President of the Chinese Supreme People’s Court, Zhou Qiang, on 9 June.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-06-17T12:21:53.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523951/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523951/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","China: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 14 March 2016 to Question 29803, what representations his Department made to the government of China at the annual UK-China Human Rights Dialogue held in April on accusations of the harvesting of organs in that country.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","39875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523952","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-17","I have received notice that Argentina’s Foreign Minister, Susana Malcorra, is bidding for the role of UN Secretary-General. We want a strong Secretary-General, one with integrity, a proven track record, first class communication skills, suitable and relevant experience and unimpeachable character. They should be committed to transparency and accountability, have strong leadership skills, a bold vision for an activist UN at the heart of the rules-based system, and be committed to cost-effective management and reform. It is imperative that any Secretary-General serves the whole membership. We judge all candidates on their merits. The United Kingdom has no doubt about its sovereignty over the Falklands and surrounding maritime areas, nor about the Falkland Islanders’ right to decide their own future.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-06-17T12:15:39.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523952/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523952/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","UN Secretariat: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has received representations to support the candidacy of Argentine Foreign Minister Susanna Malcorra for the position of UN Secretary General; what assessment he has made of the potential effect on UK sovereignty over the Falkland Islands of such an appointment; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Mr Jeffrey M. Donaldson","39873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523953","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The UK led negotiations within the Commission on the Conservation of Antarctic Marine Living Resources which resulted in the establishment of the world’s first high-seas Marine Protected Area (within the Antarctic Treaty area) and supports the establishment of further Marine Protected Areas within the area covered by the Conservation of Antarctic Marine Living Resources. The UK is also a leading member of the OSPAR Commission which has designated seven Marine Protected Areas in the high seas of the North-East Atlantic and works closely with other regional and international organisations to manage these.</p><p>The UK supports, and is fully engaged, in the work at the United Nations seeking an agreement on the conservation and sustainable use of marine biodiversity and the need to establish a mechanism to deliver marine protected areas in areas beyond national jurisdiction.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-14T14:59:08.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523953/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523953/answer","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523953/answer/previousversion/3466","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","Marine Protected Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what progress his Department has made on supporting the establishment of marine protected areas in the high seas.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","39961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523954","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The delivery of the UK Overseas Territories Blue-Belt policy is a cross-Government initiative and as such will receive cross-departmental funding.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-14T15:20:35.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523954/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523954/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","British Overseas Territories: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which departmental budget is supporting the Government's blue belt policy to protect marine biodiversity in the UK Overseas Territories.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","39962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523955","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The package of training that the Military training teams are providing to the Peshmerga includes medical instruction equivalent to the mandatory annual training for battlefield casualties that is delivered to UK troops.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-13T16:23:38.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523955/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523955/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-08","Iraq: Kurds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what medical assistance the UK provides to the Peshmerga in the Kurdistan region.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","39943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523957","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The overarching policy framework is currently being developed by Government in consultation with the UK Overseas Territories, with the objective of delivering a demonstrable increase in the protection of marine biodiversity. The UK Overseas Territories are constitutionally responsible for the conservation of their natural environments and as such will develop bespoke solutions, where necessary, to implement this policy.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-14T15:21:19.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523957/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523957/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","British Overseas Territories: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when his Department plans to publish a strategy for its blue belt policy to protect marine biodiversity in British Overseas Territories.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","40037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523958","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>Only the 1992 Protocol to the International Convention on the Establishment of an International Fund for Compensation for Oil Pollution Damage has been extended to St Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha. Information on all treaties that have been extended to the UK Overseas Territories can be found at: <a href="http://treaties.fco.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://treaties.fco.gov.uk/</a></p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-14T15:19:55.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523958/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523958/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","St Helena: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department has extended to the British Overseas Territories of St Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha the (a) International Convention on Civil Liability for Oil Pollution Damage 1969, (b) 1992 Protocol to the International Convention on the Establishment of an International Fund for Compensation for Oil Pollution Damage, (c) 2010 Protocol to the International Convention on Liability and Compensation for Damage in Connection with the Carriage of Hazardous and Noxious Substances by Sea, (d) International Convention on Civil Liability for Bunker Oil Pollution Damage 2001, (e) International Convention on Oil Pollution Preparedness, Response and Co-operation 1990 and (f) 1997 Protocol to the International Convention for the Prevention of Pollution from Ships 1973.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","40036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523959","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>We would consider whether to support any individual case for such treatment on its merits. The limited treatment provided in the UK to foreign nationals in the past has only been offered in very exceptional circumstances.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-13T16:12:08.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523959/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523959/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-08","Iraq: Kurds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will support the provision of specialist treatment at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital Birmingham for seriously injured Peshmerga from the Kurdistan region in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Bob Stewart","Beckenham","Bob Stewart","40012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523961","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-17","<p>The UK welcomes efforts to improve the UN’s recording of casualties as a means of ensuring UN decision making is better informed and civilians are better protected in conflict. We will continue to support the UN Secretary-General, the Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights and all other relevant parts of the UN system as they take this work forward. We are a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council and a strong supporter of the Human Rights Up Front Initiative.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-17T10:28:39.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523961/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523961/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","Armed Conflict: Casualties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what role the Government is playing in UN discussions on improving mechanisms for casualty recording.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","40001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523962","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>I am extremely concerned about the situation in Burundi. During my visit to Bujumbura in December 2015 I emphasised to the Burundian Government that killings, torture and other abuses must stop and that they must take action to end impunity. I underlined the need for media, opposition and civil society to be allowed to operate freely and that all sides must renounce violence and participate fully in the dialogue. I repeated these messages in my letter to the Burundian Foreign Minister in May. Our Special Envoy for the Great Lakes Region reiterated these points in meetings with Burundian ministers in Bujumbura last week and during her visit to Arusha in May for the second round of the dialogue facilitated by former Tanzanian President Mkapa.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-14T15:17:29.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523962/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523962/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-08","Burundi: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the government of Burundi on (a) ending political violence and unrest and (b) alleged extra-judicial killings, torture, lack of freedom of expression and other human rights abuses in that country.","false","Biography information for Joanna Cherry","Edinburgh South West","Joanna  Cherry","40003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523963","Department of Health","false","2016-06-13","<p>Information is not held on National Health Service spending on treating people with medical conditions caused by botox injections.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-06-13T16:36:27.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523963/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523963/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523963/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-08","Botulinum Toxin","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how  much the NHS spent on treating people with medical conditions caused by botox injections in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","40023"
